  "A quantum information scientist creates the Bell state |Phi+> = (|00> + |11>)/sqrt(2). She wants to verify it is entangled by checking if it can be written as |a>|b>. If |a> = (alpha, beta)^T and |b> = (gamma, delta)^T, then |a>|b> = (alpha*gamma, alpha*delta, beta*gamma, beta*delta)^T. For |Phi+> = (1, 0, 0, 1)^T/sqrt(2), is the state separable?": "",
